are%20over%20impressing%20the%20boss%20with%20long%20hours.%20Office%20attendance%20may%20be%20creeping%20back%20up%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-attendance-increase-5-days-mondays-fridays-data-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520report%2520found%2520increases%2520in%2Cdays%2520are%2520the%2520most%2520popular.%26amp%3Btext%3DBevi%2527s%2520data%2520suggests%2520that%2520Tuesday%2Cfor%2520workers%2520to%2520come%2520in.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFriday%20remains%20the%20least%20popular%20day%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20commute%2C%20by%20far.%20And%20as%20I%20found%2C%20for%20many%20workers%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%2C%20the%20W%20in%20WFH%20is%20in%20scare%20quotes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20search%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20TikTok%20will%20reveals%20number%20of%20viral%20hacks%20to%20trick%20your%20boss%20into%20thinking%20you're%20actively%20online.%20There%20are%20mouse%20jigglers%20and%20apps%20that%20keep%20screens%20on%20but%20also%20tips%20like%20turning%20off%20your%20phone's%20auto-caps%20settings%20so%20Slack%20messages%20look%20like%20they're%20sent%20from%20a%20computer%20and%20not%20a%20phone.%20More%20rogue%20hacks%20include%20putting%20PowerPoint%20into%20presenting%20mode%20to%20keep%20a%20screen%20on%2C%20entering%20into%20a%20Zoom%20meeting%20with%20yourself%2C%20or%20tying%20a%20mouse%20to%20an%20oscillating%20fan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20workers%20may%20appear%20to%20their%20employers%20to%20be%20online%20and%20grinding%20away%2C%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20many%20have%20shut%20their%20laptops%20and%20gone%20out%20into%20the%20world.%20In%202024%2C%20for%20example%2C%20OpenTable%20saw%2044%25%20more%20diners%20book%20reservations%20between%20noon%20and%205%20p.m.%20on%20Fridays%20than%20on%20other%20weekdays.%20%26quot%3BShifts%20in%20work%20culture%20are%20definitely%20impacting%20dining%20habits%2C%26quot%3B%20Debby%20Soo%2C%20OpenTable's%20CEO%2C%20told%20me%20over%20email.%20Similarly%2C%20on%20Resy%2C%2028%25%20of%20weekday-afternoon%20reservations%20were%20on%20Fridays%2C%20more%20than%20on%20any%20other%20weekday.%20Zocdoc%20shared%20booking%20data%20with%20me%20that%20shows%20that%20booking%20appointments%20on%20Fridays%20have%20crept%20up%20slightly%20since%202021%2C%20and%20that%20several%20types%20of%20appointments%20are%20more%20common%20on%20Fridays%2C%20including%20acupuncture%2C%20IUD%20procedures%2C%20and%20annual%20physicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActivTrak%2C%20a%20workforce-analytics%20and%20productivity-software%20company%2C%20has%20found%20that%20people%20are%20in%20fact%20calling%20it%20quits%20earlier%20on%20Fridays.%20In%20an%20analysis%20of%2071%2C000%20workers%20at%20more%20than%20800%20companies%20that%20are%20ActivTrak%20customers%2C%20the%20company%20found%20that%20in%20late%202024%20workers%20clocked%20out%20about%20an%20hour%20earlier%20on%20every%20day%20of%20the%20week%20than%20they%20did%20in%20early%202021.%20The%20steepest%20drop%20was%20on%20Fridays%2C%20with%20workers%20leaving%20at%203%3A42%20p.m.%2C%20some%2080%20minutes%20earlier%20than%20they%20did%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20may%20be%20out%20and%20about%20more%20on%20Fridays%20because%20their%20companies%20encourage%20them%20to%20log%20off.%20Buffer%2C%20a%20social%20media%20management%20software%20company%2C%20moved%20to%20a%20four-day%20workweek%20in%202020.%20It%20started%20as%20an%20experiment%20but%20proved%20so%20positive%20for%20morale%20that%20the%20company%20has%20kept%20it%20in%20place%2C%20says%20Hailley%20Griffis%2C%20its%20head%20of%20communications%20and%20content.%20After%20the%20initial%20adjustment%20of%20cramming%20more%20meetings%20into%20the%20first%20four%20days%20of%20the%20week%2C%20the%20schedule%20now%20%26quot%3Breally%20helps%20reduce%20the%20amount%20of%20stress%20and%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20go%20back%20to%20working%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20energy%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStok%2C%20a%20sustainability%20consulting%20company%2C%20started%20offering%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20Fridays%26quot%3B%20every%20other%20week%20in%202020.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20have%20no%20emails%20or%20meetings%20that%20day%2C%20and%20instead%20allow%20employees%20to%20put%20their%20heads%20down%20on%20projects%20or%20take%20the%20day%20for%20themselves%2C%20says%20Madeleine%20Drake%2C%20Stok's%20director%20of%20people%20and%20culture.%20%26quot%3BEach%20of%20us%20has%20the%20awareness%20and%20autonomy%20and%20collaborative%20spirit%20to%20understand%20what's%20best%20each%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20some%2090%25%20of%20the%20company's%20employees%20typically%20participate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20flexible%20gigs%20are%20getting%20harder%20to%20come%20by.%20Job%20posts%20offering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-fears-job-cuts-employers-less-flexible-with-workers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efour-day%20workweeks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20dropped%2042%25%20since%20late%202022%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Indeed%2C%20and%20those%20offering%20flexible%20Fridays%20are%20down%2018.5%25.%20Employees%20are%20likely%20%26quot%3Bmore%20interested%20than%20they've%20ever%20been%26quot%3B%20in%20flexible%20Fridays%20and%20shorter%20workweeks%2C%20Kyle%20M.K.%2C%20Indeed's%20talent-strategy%20advisor%2C%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20implementation%20is%20probably%20slowing%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20part%20due%20to%20economic%20pressures%20and%20labor%20market%20uncertainty%2C%20he%20adds.%20There's%20a%20disconnect%20between%20what%20employees%20want%20and%20what%20employers%20are%20offering%2C%20despite%20growing%20evidence%20that%20shorter%20workweeks%20improve%20productivity%20and%20employee%20satisfaction%20and%20that%20workers%20are%20getting%20fewer%20things%20done%20on%20Fridays%20anyway.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20employers%20will%20start%20to%20see%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20ability%20to%20attract%20top%20talent%20and%20see%20their%20turnover%20grow%20if%20they're%20not%20focusing%20on%20the%20work-life%20balance%2C%20the%20burnout%2C%20and%20the%20stress%20level%20of%20their%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20feel%20there's%20no%20reason%20to%20hang%20around%20on%20Fridays%20if%20they%20can%20get%20all%20their%20work%20done%20by%20Thursday.%20Jenna%2C%20who%20works%20in%20sales%20in%20Philadelphia%20and%20whose%20name%20has%20also%20been%20changed%2C%20says%20she%20felt%20burnout%20in%202020%20and%20would%20have%20to%20log%20off%20midday%20because%20of%20exhaustion.%20Nearly%20five%20years%20later%2C%20she's%20taking%20nearly%20all%20of%20Friday%20off%20and%20expects%20her%20clients%20or%20coworkers%20to%20be%20doing%20little%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20workweek%2C%20too.%20Like%20Annie%2C%20she%20chats%20with%20me%20on%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%20%E2%80%94%20between%20hanging%20out%20at%20a%20neighborhood%20brewery%20and%20running%20an%20errand.%20It's%20a%20typical%20Friday%20for%20her%2C%20which%20can%20include%20vet%20appointments%20for%20her%20dog%2C%20trips%20to%20the%20gym%2C%20or%20boozy%20lunches%20with%20a%20friend.%20%26quot%3BA%20Friday-morning%20Costco%20run%20is%20magical%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenna%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20trust%20gap%20between%20bosses%20and%20workers%20is%20widening.%20A%202024%20survey%20from%20PwC%20found%20that%2086%25%20of%20business%20executives%20believe%20employee%20trust%20to%20be%20high%2C%20but%20just%2067%25%20of%20employees%20say%20they%20have%20high%20trust%20in%20their%20employer.%20About%20half%20of%20business%20executives%20say%20they%20have%20a%20great%20extent%20of%20trust%20for%20senior%20leadership%2C%20while%20just%2038%25%20say%20the%20same%20of%20entry-level%20workers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployment%20is%20a%20contract%2C%20where%20both%20parties%20should%20have%20clear%20communication%20to%20maintain%20trust%2C%20says%20Shaun%20Hansen%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Western%20Oregon%20University.%20If%20you're%20instructed%20or%20it's%20implied%20that%20you%20should%20be%20working%20Fridays%2C%20then%20that's%20the%20agreement.%20But%20employers%20can%20build%20trust%20by%20better%20communicating%20their%20expectations%20and%20shifting%20to%20more%20flexible%20arrangements%2C%20Hansen%20says.%20That%20might%20mean%20analyzing%20roles%20and%20admitting%20that%20not%20every%20white%20collar%20job%20has%20to%20fit%20a%2040-hour%2C%209-to-5%20schedule%20to%20be%20done%20well.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20job%20that%20you%20can%20finish%20on%20a%20Thursday%20night%2C%20but%20your%20employer%20is%20insisting%20that%20you're%20there%20on%20Friday%2C%20it%20not%20only%20puts%20you%20in%20an%20ethical%20pickle%2C%20but%20it%20also%20will%20cause%20you%20to%20probably%20look%20for%20a%20better%20job%20where%20you%20have%20more%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20no-work%20Fridays%20are%20a%20privilege%20reserved%20for%20white-collar%20remote%20or%20hybrid%20workers.%20The%20more%20room%20they%20have%20to%20slack%20off%2C%20the%20greater%20a%20divide%20we%20might%20see%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-who-hate-phrase-work-life-balance-prefer-alternative-views-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20industries.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20guilty%20about%20it%20from%20the%20level%20of%3A%20What%20a%20privilege%20I%20have%20that%20I%20have%20a%20job%20that%20I%20can%20even%20do%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenna%20tells%20me.%20But%20guilt%20about%20not%20being%20fully%20honest%20with%20her%20employer%20as%20she%20fields%20occasional%20Microsoft%20Teams%20pings%20from%20the%20bar%3F%20Not%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%20last%20summer%2C%20a%20friend%20and%20I%20packed%20up%20the%20car%20to%20head%20away%20for%20the%20weekend.%20I%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20my%20then-employer's%20summer%20Fridays%2C%20left%20my%20laptop%20at%20home.%20But%20I%20watched%20as%20my%20friend%20connected%20her%20laptop%20to%20a%20hot%20spot%2C%20opened%20it%20on%20the%20back%20seat%2C%20and%20began%20playing%20a%20lengthy%20fireplace%20video%20on%20YouTube%20that%20would%20keep%20the%20green%20circle%20next%20to%20her%20face%20on%20Slack%20aglow%20for%20the%20ride.%20I%20was%20given%20her%20phone%20to%20act%20not%20just%20as%20a%20road-trip%20DJ%20but%20also%20as%20her%20secretary%2C%20responding%20to%20any%20messages%20from%20her%20boss.%20It%20took%20some%20teamwork%2C%20but%20where%20there's%20a%20will%20to%20work%20less%2C%20there's%20a%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsneaky-rise-no-work-fridays-long-weekends-burnout-zero-remorse-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737018602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67853b62e294a7514e8cc3e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsneaky-rise-no-work-fridays-long-weekends-burnout-zero-remorse-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Remote%20workers%20are%20secr