ment%20Centers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbernie-marcus-billionaire-founder-home-depot-trump-donor-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarcus%2C%20who%20died%20at%2095%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202024%20with%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20more%20than%20%2410%20billion%2C%20served%20as%20Handy%20Dan's%20president.%20Blank%2C%20now%2082%20and%20worth%20over%20%249%20billion%2C%20was%20the%20company's%20treasurer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus%20and%20Blank%20were%20fired%20in%201978%20after%20Handy%20Dan's%20corporate%20parent%20said%20in%20securities%20filings%20that%20it%20found%20%26quot%3Bunauthorized%20and%20unacceptable%20business%20practices%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20company%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%20Handy%20Dan's%20corporate%20parent%20later%20said%20the%20two%20men%20used%20company%20funds%20to%20pay%20employees%20to%20favor%20union%20decertification%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20began%20investigating%20in%20late%201978%20after%20a%20lawyer%20for%20a%20retail%20workers%20labor%20union%20filed%20a%20complaint%20to%20federal%20authorities%20based%20on%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20agents%20said%20their%20investigation%20substantiated%20the%20claim%2C%20according%20to%20the%20records.%20No%20charges%20were%20ever%20brought%3B%20the%20records%20cited%20%26quot%3Binsufficient%26quot%3B%20evidence%20and%20%26quot%3Bstatute%20of%20limitations%20problems.%26quot%3B%20The%20effort%20to%20decertify%20the%20union%20was%20ultimately%20unsuccessful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestigation%20revealed%20that%20from%20early%201977%20through%20early%201978%20approximately%20%24140%2C000%20in%20corporate%20funds%26quot%3B%20were%20paid%20to%20workers%20to%20influence%20them%2C%20an%20FBI%20agent%20wrote%20in%20a%20memo.%20%26quot%3BNumerous%20employees%20have%20admitted%20receiving%20cash%20(over%20and%20above%20wages)%20usually%20received%20in%20plain%20envelopes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20interviewed%20at%20least%20eight%20witnesses%2C%20whose%20names%20were%20largely%20redacted%20in%20the%20records.%20One%20anti-union%20employee%20told%20investigators%20that%20money%20%26quot%3Bwas%20only%20furnished%20to%20those%20whom%20the%20company%20thought%20would%20eventually%20vote%20for%20the%20decertification.%26quot%3B%20Clinton%20Doolen%2C%20a%20manager%20who%20died%20in%201992%2C%20recalled%20Marcus%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bmoney%20was%20no%20object%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20came%20to%20dislodging%20the%20union%2C%20the%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarcus%20was%20strictly%20against%20the%20unions%20and%20highly%20obsessed%20with%20getting%20the%20union%20completely%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20witness%20told%20the%20FBI.%20The%20witness%20said%20Marcus%20told%20them%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20use%20any%20means%20to%20break%20the%20union%2C%20and%20the%20witness%20%26quot%3Bcould%20see%20that%20Marcus%20really%20meant%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus%20offered%20a%20different%20version%20of%20events.%20In%20the%201999%20book%20%26quot%3BBuilt%20From%20Scratch%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20he%20learned%20some%20Handy%20Dan%20employees%20wanted%20to%20disband%20their%20union.%20He%20said%20he%20hired%20a%20lawyer%20and%20%26quot%3Bdirected%20our%20personnel%20department%20to%20do%20whatever%20fell%20within%20the%20legal%20guidelines%26quot%3B%20to%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20chairman%20of%20Handy%20Dan's%20parent%20company%20twisted%20the%20truth%20and%20used%20an%20internal%20investigation%20%26quot%3Bas%20a%20tool%20to%20eliminate%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bneither%20the%20Justice%20Department%20nor%20the%20SEC%20instigated%20investigations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFBI%20records%20show%20Marcus%20testified%20in%20a%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20proceeding%20in%20July%201978%2C%20about%20three%20months%20after%20he%20was%20fired.%20He%20declined%2C%20through%20a%20lawyer%2C%20to%20be%20interviewed%20by%20the%20FBI.%20It's%20not%20clear%20if%20Blank%20was%20a%20subject%20of%20inquiry%20by%20the%20SEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SEC%20and%20two%20top-ranking%20officials%20at%20the%20Marcus%20Foundation%20didn't%20reply%20to%20comment%20requests%2C%20nor%20did%20Marcus'%20son%20Frederick%20Marcus%2C%20who%20is%20a%20director%20of%20the%20foundation.%20Representatives%20for%20Blank%2C%20Home%20Depot%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%20and%20the%20FBI%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20obtained%20the%20FBI%20records%20in%20response%20to%20a%20Freedom%20of%20Information%20Act%20request.%20Blank's%20name%20was%20redacted%2C%20but%20his%20job%20title%20matched%20that%20of%20the%20subject%20in%20question.%20A%20third%20person%20whose%20name%20was%20redacted%20was%20also%20a%20subject%20of%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20submitted%20a%20%26quot%3Bprosecutive%20report%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department%20in%20March%201982.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20a%20federal%20prosecutor%20decided%20not%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20case.%20The%20prosecutor%20didn't%20believe%20there%20was%20enough%20evidence%20against%20Marcus%2C%20Blank%2C%20and%20the%20third%20person%20to%20indict%20them%2C%20and%20the%20union%20election%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20investigation%20was%20more%20than%20five%20years%20old%2C%20an%20FBI%20memo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus%20and%20Blank%20founded%20Home%20Depot%20in%201978%2C%20eventually%20transforming%20it%20into%20the%20world's%20largest%20home-improvement%20retail%20company.%20Its%20stores%20aren't%20unionized%3B%20in%202022%2C%20the%20last%20time%20a%20petition%20was%20filed%20at%20a%20store%20for%20a%20union%20election%2C%20union%20advocates%20suffered%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fcase%2F04-RC-303670%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresounding%20defeat%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcus'%20anti-union%20sentiments%20were%20well%20known.%20In%202008%2C%20he%20called%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20employees%20to%20form%20unions%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB122705706314639537%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20demise%20of%20civilization%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20in%202010%2C%20he%20founded%20the%20Job%20Creators%20Network%2C%20which%20has%20opposed%20bills%20that%20would%20increase%20union%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20men%20have%20been%20significant%20political%20donors.%20Blank%20has%20primarily%20supported%20Democratic%20candidates%2C%20while%20Marcus%20gave%20millions%20to%20Republican%20candidates%2C%20and%20once%20said%20that%20retail%20executives%20who%20weren't%20helping%20Republicans%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20shot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20the%20documents%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25479375-bernard-marcus-fbi-file%2F%3Fembed%3D1%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-depot-cofounders-1970s-fbi-investigation-bribery-allegations-union-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737018062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67881bed50dfd88e193ea5fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-depot-cofounders-1970s-fbi-investigation-bribery-allegations-union-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bernie%20Marcus%20and%20Arthur%20Blank%20were%20once%20investigated%20over%20claims%20of%20cash%20handed%20out%20in%20%26quot%3Bplain%20envelopes.%26quot%3B%20No%2