ise%20basic%20pay%20for%20US%20troops%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%204.5%25%20across%20the%20board%2C%20citing%20concerns%20about%20recruitment%20difficulties%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-american-army-soldiers-complain-food-pay-tiktok-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20insecurity%20among%20soldiers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Junior%20enlisted%20troops%2C%20who%20hold%20rank%20equivalents%20of%20E-1%20to%20E-4%2C%20received%20an%20even%20bigger%20raise%20of%2014.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-military-service-members-make-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etroops%20were%20earning%20less%20than%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20basic%20pay%2C%20and%20the%20bill%20passed%20in%20December%20aimed%20to%20raise%20their%20salaries%20to%20that%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20uses%20a%20different%20metric%20that%20extends%20beyond%20basic%20pay%2C%20which%20it%20calls%20regular%20military%20compensation.%20This%20includes%20benefits%20such%20as%20tax%20advantages%20and%20housing%20and%20food%20allowances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20that%20measure%2C%20the%20Defense%20Department's%20new%20report%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bmilitary%20pay%20among%20Junior%20Enlisted%20Personnel%20is%20higher%20than%2090th%20percentile%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwages-outpace-inflation-consumer-sentiment-high-prices-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearnings%20for%20civilians%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20similar%20education%20and%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasic%20pay%20is%20a%20blunt%20and%20costly%20instrument%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20should%20be%20used%20only%20when%20there%20are%20system-wide%20problems%2C%20such%20as%20widespread%20retention%20and%20recruiting%20shortfalls%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20solved%20more%20efficiently%20with%20other%20policy%20instruments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20findings%20relied%20largely%20on%20a%20benchmark%20that%20compared%20two%20things%3A%20the%2070th%20percentile%20of%20compensation%20for%20enlisted%20soldiers%20and%20the%2070th%20percentile%20earnings%20for%20full-time%20civilian%20workers%20with%20the%20same%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20for%20enlisted%20soldiers%20with%20one%20year%20of%20service%2C%20the%20top%2070th%20percentile%20received%20about%20%241%2C000%20a%20week%20in%20regular%20military%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20report%20listed%20the%2070th%20percentile%20of%20civilian%20earners%20as%20needing%2010%20years%20of%20work%20experience%20to%20get%20%241%2C000%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20said%20that%20for%20enlisted%20soldiers%20with%2010%20years%20of%20service%2C%20the%20top%2070th%20percentile%20of%20earners%20gets%20%241%2C500%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%2070th%20percentile%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-pay-housing-college-education-benefits-signing-bonus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eofficer%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20stands%20at%20%241%2C500%20a%20week%20for%20those%20with%20one%20year%20of%20service%2C%20going%20up%20to%20nearly%20%242%2C500%20a%20week%20for%20those%20with%2010%20years%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20compared%20those%20earnings%20to%20the%2070th%20percentile%20of%20civilians%20with%20college%20degrees%2C%20whom%20the%20report%20said%20consistently%20earn%20about%20%24200%20to%20%24300%20less%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20enlisted%20personnel%20earn%20more%20than%2083%20out%20of%20100%20civilian%20workers%20with%20the%20same%20education%20and%20experience%2C%20and%20officers%20earn%20more%20than%2076%20out%20of%20100%20civilian%20workers%20with%20the%20same%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20mostly%20recommended%20%26quot%3Bquality-